In a skillet, heat butter or oil over medium-high heat. Add potatoes and cook just until they begin to brown. Transfer to slow cooker stoneware. Reduce heat to medium. Add onions and cook, stirring, until softened. Add garlic, curry powder, salt and peppercorns. Stir and cook for 1 minute. Add water or stock, bring to a boil and pour over potatoes. Cover and cook on Low for 8 hours or on High for 4 hours, until potatoes are tender. Stir in lemon juice and garnish with cilantro.